{"article_id":"3ZTBoNTDOc2hGcb3","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"A year after President Obama warned the Syrian regime","depth":8},{"id":1,"text":"that using chemical weapons would cross a `` red line ,","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"''","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"Syrian activists are accusing Bashar Assad 's forces of killing hundreds in a gas attack","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"-- in what would be the worst and deadliest chemical attack to date .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"The attack raises new concerns","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"that the so-called `` red line '' in Syria has been crossed ,","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"violated","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"and effectively ignored .","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"The situation compounds the Mideast challenges","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"facing the Obama administration ,","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"as his national security team continues to deliberate on how to handle the unrest in Egypt","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"-- another trouble spot","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"where the U.S. is keeping itself at a distance .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"White House spokesman Josh Earnest said in a statement Wednesday","depth":5},{"id":15,"text":"that the U.S. is `` deeply concerned '' by the reports in Syria","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"and is calling for a United Nations probe .","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"`` We are working urgently","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"to gather additional information , ''","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"he said .","depth":6},{"id":20,"text":"`` The United States strongly condemns any and all use of chemical weapons .","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"Those responsible for the use of chemical weapons must be held accountable .","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"Today , we are formally requesting","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"that the United Nations urgently investigate this new allegation .","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"The U.N. investigative team ,","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"which is currently in Syria ,","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"is prepared to do so ,","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"and that is consistent with its purpose and mandate . ''","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"Daily politics news delivered to your inbox :","depth":3},{"id":29,"text":"sign up for our newsletter","depth":3},{"id":30,"text":"The U.N. Security Council met late Wednesday afternoon on the allegations","depth":6},{"id":31,"text":"and called for `` a thorough , impartial and prompt investigation . ''","depth":6},{"id":32,"text":"Diplomats told the Associated Press","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"that during the two-hour closed session , Russia and China ,","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"which support the Syrian government ,","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"blocked a stronger press statement","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"supported by Britain , France , the U.S. and others .","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"A newly disclosed letter from U.S. Gen. Martin Dempsey , chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff , makes clear","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"that the U.S. is not interested in taking military action at this point","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"to stop Assad .","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"Effectively ruling out U.S. cruise missile attacks and other options","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"that would n't require U.S. troops on the ground ,","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"Dempsey said","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"the military is clearly capable","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"of taking out Assad 's air force","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"and shifting the balance of the Arab country 's 2 1/2-year war back toward the armed opposition .","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"But he said","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"such an approach would plunge the United States deep into another war in the Arab world","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"and offer no strategy for peace in a nation","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"plagued by ethnic rivalries .","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"`` Syria today is not about choosing between two sides ,","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"but rather about choosing one among many sides , ''","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"Dempsey said in a letter Aug. 19 to Rep. Eliot Engel , D-N.Y.","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"`` It is my belief","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"that the side","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"we choose","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"must be ready to promote their interests and ours","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"when the balance shifts in their favor .","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"Today , they are not . ''","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"Engel said , in response to the letter ,","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"that he remains `` deeply unsatisfied '' with the current strategy ,","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"`` as we stand on the sidelines","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"when the turmoil in that country continues to claim thousands of lives","depth":13},{"id":63,"text":"and sow instability throughout the region . '' `` I reject the notion","depth":13},{"id":64,"text":"that our involvement in Syria would simply constitute 'choosing sides ' between one armed group and another , ''","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"he said in a statement .","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"`` Rather , our involvement represents a choice","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"between hastening the end of the Assad regime","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"or continuing to allow the cycle of violence , displacement , and terror to continue unabated . ''","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"Reuters reported estimates from Syrian activists","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"that more than 200 were killed on Wednesday","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"after rockets hit an area in the Damascus suburbs .","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"Syrian state television has denied any use of poison gas by the Assad government .","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"Another group claimed","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"nearly 500 were killed .","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"The Syrian National Coalition put the death toll at more than 600 ,","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"according to AFP .","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"The claims came","depth":6},{"id":78,"text":"as a 20-member U.N. chemical weapons team was in Syria","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"to investigate three sites","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"where chemical weapons attacks allegedly had occurred in the past .","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"State media quoted a government official","depth":5},{"id":82,"text":"claiming","depth":6},{"id":83,"text":"the latest allegations were a bid","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"to `` divert the U.N . commission . ''","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"The Obama administration has defended its response to date in Syria .","depth":5},{"id":86,"text":"Since Obama declared last August","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"that chemical weapons would constitute a `` red line , ''","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"the administration this past June did conclude","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"that the government used chemical weapons .","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"Following that ,","depth":7},{"id":91,"text":"the president authorized military support for the Syrian opposition .","depth":7},{"id":92,"text":"But that is still in the works ,","depth":5},{"id":93,"text":"and Dempsey cautioned","depth":7},{"id":94,"text":"against going any further , namely out of concern","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"that there 's no clear entity with a strong chance","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"of succeeding","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"to get behind .","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"`` It is a deeply rooted , long-term conflict among multiple factions ,","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"and violent struggles for power will continue","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"after Assad 's rule ends , ''","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"he wrote .","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"`` We should evaluate the effectiveness of limited military options in this context . ''","depth":7},{"id":103,"text":"Asked if Assad is any closer to being forced from power ,","depth":5},{"id":104,"text":"White House spokesman Josh Earnest reiterated Tuesday","depth":7},{"id":105,"text":"that that is a `` goal ''","depth":7},{"id":106,"text":"and defended the U.S. response .","depth":6},{"id":107,"text":"`` I think","depth":7},{"id":108,"text":"that there is no doubt","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"that there is pretty broad international consensus about Mr. Assad and his regime and his need","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"to leave power , ''","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"he said .","depth":6},{"id":112,"text":"`` So I think","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"on that front ,","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"yes , some progress has been made .","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"But there 's no doubt","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"that what 's ongoing there continues to be a terrible situation . ''","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":233,"left":146,"right":232,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":146,"left":144,"right":145,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":144,"left":130,"right":143,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":130,"left":125,"right":129,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":125,"left":121,"right":124,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":121,"left":119,"right":120,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":119,"left":118,"right":2,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":118,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":120,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":124,"left":5,"right":123,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"left":6,"right":122,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":122,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":129,"left":126,"right":128,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":126,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":11,"right":127,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":127,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":143,"left":132,"ri